About Our School

Gandhi Adarsh H.Sec. School
Rewa's Pride Since 1989

Gandhi Adarsh Higher Secondary School (GAHS), Rewa, was established in 1989 with a vision to nurture curious, knowledgeable, and compassionate learners. Located at Ratahara, Rewa (M.P.), we offer Hindi and English medium education from Nursery to Class XII.

We aim to shape confident, independent global citizens who value empathy, respect, and lifelong learning ‚Äî contributing to a better and more peaceful world. Our school is built on strong academic foundations, sports excellence, and creative growth.

The school provides the highest standards of education, infrastructure, and holistic development at fees that every family in Rewa can comfortably afford.

Mrs. Manokamna Tiwari
Principal ‚Äî Gandhi Adarsh H.Sec. School, Rewa

Enquire for Admission

Documents Required for Admission

Please keep the following documents ready when applying for admission at Gandhi Adarsh Higher Secondary School. Kindly bring original documents along with self-attested photocopies.

1

Mark Sheet of Previous Academic Year

Official mark sheet / result card from the last attended academic year.

2

Transfer Certificate (TC)

Transfer Certificate issued by the previous school, duly signed by the principal.

3

Birth Certificate of the Student

Official birth certificate for age verification, issued by municipal authority or hospital.

4

Identity Proof of Parent & Child

Aadhaar Card, PAN Card, Voter ID or any other government-issued identity document for both parent and child.

5

Passport-Sized Photographs

Two recent passport-sized photographs of the student with a white or light background.

6

Caste Certificate (if applicable)

Valid caste certificate issued by the competent authority for SC / ST / OBC categories.

7

Medical Certificate

Certificate mentioning the student's blood group, known allergies, and any special health conditions or requirements.

8

Address Proof

Utility bill, rent agreement, Aadhaar card, or any official document showing the current residential address.

9

Report Card / Progress Report (mid-session transfer)

Latest progress report or report card required if the student is transferring mid-session from another school.

10

Migration Certificate (if applicable)

Required for students applying from other boards (e.g., CBSE, ICSE) to Madhya Pradesh Board (MPBSE).
